# Git safety

Repo identity: detect at runtime — `gh repo view --json nameWithOwner -q .nameWithOwner` (fallback: parse `git remote get-url origin`).

## When to commit or push

- Only create commits when the user **explicitly** asks (e.g. "commit", "commit and push").
- Do **not** auto-commit after edits or at end of session.
- Push only when the user explicitly asks to push (commit-only is valid).

## Never commit

- `token.md`, `*token*.md`, `.env`, `.env.*`
- `*credentials*.json`, `*service-account*.json`, `*.pem`, `*.key`
- `application_default_credentials.json`, `.gcloud/`

Warn the user if they request committing any of these.

## Forbidden git operations

- Never `git push --force` to `main` or `master` (warn if user requests)
- Never `git config` changes
- Never `--no-verify` / `--no-gpg-sign` unless user explicitly requests
- Avoid `git commit --amend` unless user rules amend conditions are all met

## Push from Cursor (macOS)

Before `git push` in the agent terminal:

```bash
unset GIT_ASKPASS SSH_ASKPASS
export GIT_TERMINAL_PROMPT=1
```

On 401 / auth failure, read `gh-docs/git-push-authentication.md`.

Push blocked by Cursor **Auto-review** (not auth): retry the same `git push` with Smart Mode approval — see `agentic-workflows/git-commit-push.md#cursor-auto-review-push-to-main`.

## PR and merge

- Full PR path: `.cursor/skills/git-feature-pr/SKILL.md` — branch `feature/<topic>`, base `main`, merge after explicit user request (solo) or GitHub approval (team)
- **Solo:** explicit *"merge the PR"* after reviewing diff — GitHub does not allow self-approval
- **Team:** create `.github/require-pr-approval`; require `reviewDecision: APPROVED` from a non-author reviewer
- Never `gh pr merge` without user asking
- Never auto-merge

